While IIT asserts that a higher \( \Phi \) indicates higher consciousness, it struggles with applicability to systems like computers or simple organisms, which may exhibit substantial integration without consciousness. This is evident in contradictions like C9 versus C13, revealing gaps in detailing why integrated information equates to conscious awareness specifically, and not just to general complexity.

